{
  "text": "FFs are usually characterized by a lower diffusion of managerial mechanisms, because of widespread entrepreneurship, and strong linkages between the family and the enterprise [CITATION_1] . We strengthened the assumptions of [CITATION_2] , who observed a gap in current frameworks concerning the role of performance measurement systems, in particular about the use of the strategic planning and management control systems.",
